          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Surrounding the implantation point was the",
                "Summing NaI detector SuN. SuN is a cylindrical",
                "NaI(Tl) scintillator, 16 inches in height and 16",
                "inches in diameter, with a 1.7 inch borehole along",
                "its axis. SuN is segmented into eight, optically",
                "isolated segments, four above and four below the beam",
                "axis."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Plastic scintillation detector was placed in",
                "focal plane of A1900 fragment separator to measure",
                "time of flight and energy loss for event-by-event",
                "idetification of 69Co ions."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Si PIN detectors located upstream of the",
                "implantation point were used for time of flight",
                "measurement for ion identification."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The beam ions were implanted in a 1 mm thick",
                "double sided silicon strip detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The present work reports on indirect measurement",
                "that provides strong constraints on the",
                "68Ni(n,gamma)69Ni reaction rate. Population of",
                "compound nucleus 69Ni via the beta decay of 69Co and",
                "measuring the gamma-ray deexcitation of excited",
                "states in 69Ni. The beta-Oslo method was used to",
                "extract the gamma-ray strength function and the",
                "nuclear level density."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 86Kr primary beam was accelerated to 140 MeV/A at",
                "the Coupled Cyclotron Facility, and was impinged on a",
                "Be production target. The A1900 fragment separator",
                "was used to select the isotope of interest 69Co as",
                "part of a cocktail consisting of approximately twelve",
                "isotopes in this mass region. 69Co ions were identified",
                "event-by-event based on energy loss and time-of-flight",
                "information"
              ]
            }
          ],
